            <div class="card-body" style="padding: 20px;">
              <h2 class="card-title">4. THERE’S NO MCDONALD’S</h2><hr style="border-top: 1px solid gray;">
                <p class="card-text">
                    Along with armed forces, another thing you’re unlikely to see in Iceland is a Big Mac.</p>
                <p class="card-text">
                    McDonald’s used to have a small handful of branches in Reykjavik, and indeed, the famous burger franchise was a success at first. However, after the initial honeymoon period, business diminished. And – even more importantly – after the financial crash in 2008, ingredients imported to Iceland soared in price, with the McDonald’s food following suit. This led to a domino effect and ultimately the shutting down of McDonalds restaurants in Iceland.</p>
                <p class="card-text">
                    The last cheeseburger sold in Iceland is still on display as a museum exhibit. Visitors to the National Museum in Iceland can see the meal, dating back to 2009, encased in glass.</p>
                <p style="font-size: 12pt; color: gray;">https://adventures.is/information/iceland-facts/</p>
            </div>
